reviews.text: Good spot facing the sea and boats. Not expensive seafoods, lunch and dinner sets. Common Chinese dishes. Lots of customers. Eight minutes from ferry pier.
Price is reasonable for what is has to offer. Seafood was ok, not the best u have in HK but acceptable. The soya sauce noodle was surprisingly good. We returned the clams coz was full of sand ...
Your average 茶餐廳 but nice location by the water.
The food was good

Seafood ok, not very expensive, but also not the best in Hong Kong.

Around HKD100 per dish. Local nice environment as you can seat outside eating, while enjoying  the special seaview of Cheung Chou with a lot of fishermen boats there.

Have the feel of small fishing village in Hong Kong.
